SapuraCrest, Macarthur, SingTel: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-06-30T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/sapuracrest-macarthur-singtel-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding  Japan .
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Eversendai Corp. (EVSD MK): Shares of the Malaysian
structural steel contractor will make its debut on the Kuala
Lumpur stock exchange. The company sold shares to institutions
at 1.70 ringgit each and 1.62 ringgit to individual investors in
its initial public offering.  SapuraCrest Petroleum Bhd. (SCRES)  : The Malaysian oil
and gas services provider said profit in the first quarter ended
April 30 rose 43 percent from a year earlier to 72.3 million
ringgit, according to a stock exchange filing. The stock added 1
percent to 4.20 ringgit.  Macarthur Coal Ltd. (MCC)  :  Macarthur Coal  said the
selldown of the Codrilla project to the Coppabella Moorvale
Joint Venture has concluded. Completion of the transaction
confirms Macarthur Coal’s profit guidance for the 2011 financial
year in the range of A$240 million to A$260 million, the company
said. The shares gained 2.8 percent to A$10.95.  Singapore Telecommunications Ltd. (ST)  : Southeast Asia’s
biggest phone company signed a $2.16 billion loan which matures
in June 2014, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Funds
from the revolving credit facility will be used for general
corporate purposes, the data show. The shares rose 2.3 percent
to S$3.16.  Seek Ltd. (SEK)  : Seek Asia Ltd. will acquire an
additional 20 percent of JobsDB Inc., increasing its holding to
80 percent, Seek said in a regulatory filing. The consideration
payable on completion is HK$600 million. Seek rose 4 percent to
$A6.44.  To contact the reporter on this story:
